    <h2>The model shapes everything</h2>

    <p>
        Latency, accuracy, GPU requirements, language support, privacy — all of
        it flows from your model choice. The good news: in 2026, every tier is
        genuinely excellent. The question is matching the model to your hardware
        and workflow.
    </p>

    <p>
        For an objective view of where models stand, the <a
            href="https://huggingface.co/spaces/hf-audio/open_asr_leaderboard"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener">Open ASR Leaderboard</a
        > on Hugging Face tracks Word Error Rate (WER) across standardised benchmarks.
        It's the most reliable public signal for comparing transcription accuracy
        across models.
    </p>

    <h2>Cohere Transcribe</h2>

    <p>
        <strong
